<title>MEXICO: Mexico's Nafin sets credit program for small firms.</title>
<headline>Mexico's Nafin sets credit program for small firms.</headline>
<dateline>MEXICO CITY 1997-06-08</dateline>
<text>
<p>Mexican development bank Nacional Financiera (Nafin) said on Sunday it set up with Banorte an approximately one billion peso credit program for small and medium-sized businesses.</p>
<p>Loans for smaller companies of up to 500,000 pesos for as long as five years will be available through 1997, Nafin said.</p>
<p>Nafin director Carlos Sales Gutierrez also said the development bank would soon offer a five-year fixed rate credit program for small and medium-size businesses.</p>
<p>((--Timna Tanners, Mexico City newsroom +525 728-7903))</p>
